content: What 1960s British rock band had members named Roger Daltrey, Pete Townshend, John Entwistle, and Keith Moon?

The 1960s British rock band with members Roger Daltrey, Pete Townshend, John Entwistle, and Keith Moon is The Who. The Who is known for their high-energy live performances and classic rock anthems such as "My Generation," " Baba O'Riley," and "Won't Get Fooled Again." The band was formed in 1964 and became one of the most influential rock bands of the 20th century.
